# 0.2.7 Changelog
## [Difficulty]
+ Added a brand new difficulty system
+ Added two new difficulty presets: Hard and Legendary.
+ Added a difficulty customizer; tweak many different game parameters

## [Hard Mode]
An easier version of MiTE.
+ Starts with 5 hearts and hunger as minimum
+ Mining speed is increased by 50%
+ Mobs do 25% less damage to the player
+ Animals/Mobs will always drop their loot no matter the cause of death
+ Weather events do not occur until after the 16th day in a world
+ Cave-ins can no longer be caused by walking on unstable ground

## [Legendary Mode]
A more brutal version of MiTE.
+ Leaf blocks are non solid, gravity blocks break them
+ Vines can no longer be climbed, only used for descent
+ You earn a new heart and hunger pip per 7 levels (normally 5)
+ Your hearts and hunger cap out at 8
+ Mobs deal 50% more damage
+ The player deals 25% less damage
+ There is no weather grace period

## [General]
+ Workbenches now scale crafting speed based on tier, with huge increases in mithril and especially adamantium
+ Chickens now use worms as their breeding item; previously it was way too easy to scale up chicken farms
+ Revenants and Bone Lords sounds have been pitched down, for better audio indication of their presence
+ Weather events do not occur for 8 days when starting a world
+ Item frames and signs can now be placed on chests
+ Added an additional sound for when mobs "poof"
+ Tweaked how the ingame display is rendered; bottom elements are raised slightly towards the center
+ Fixed music display rendering leak, should no longer flicker when enchanted gear is in the inventory
+ Fixed buckets crashing when using other mods that add buckets (e.g. ITF)
+ Fixed buckets restoring themselves when making cheese and bowls of water

## [Stack Size Changes]
+ Increased stack size for ores (4 -> 8)
+ Increased stack size for glass (4 -> 8)
+ Increased stack size for bookshelves (4 -> 8)
+ Increased stack size for TNT (4 -> 8)
+ Increased stack size for wood slabs (8 -> 16)

