# 0.2.6 Changelog
## [General]
+ Data driven music system overhaul. Additional details can be found in mod assets file ``assets/miterenewed/MUSIC.md``
+ Added 8 new songs from C418 that play under various conditions
+ Temporary config file system, allowing you to set music frequency
+ Most buckets now use a durability system instead of a random break chance system
+ Buckets now take damage when placing lava, and when lava buckets are used in smelting
+ Buckets now take damage when removing Cobblestone from them
+ Buckets no longer stack
+ Sandstone Oven has been renamed to Sandstone Furnace
+ Sandstone Furnace is now able to smelt ores like the Stone Furnace can
+ Charcoal is now hot enough to smelt ores
+ Charcoal burn time has been decreased to 4 items, and now only crafts into 2 torches
+ Leads can now be crafted with all slime types
+ Fixed auto use crashing when item becomes empty

## [Development]
+ Added new hook for allowing damaged item in crafting recipes
+ Edited a few repair related methods/recipe parsing to fix some oversights in vanilla code

# 0.2.5 Changelog
## [General]
+ Gravel drops have been reworked so that only flint and flint chips will drop when mining with gravel your fist
+ Handpans can now be automatically used by holding RMB and pressing LMB
+ Added new localized logo art for Chinese language
+ Added new music tracks from C418: Moog City, Moog City 2, Équinoxe
+ Added particles to manure when used on farmland
+ Reduced the time it takes for most cutting recipes to complete
+ Reduced mesh recipe from 6 components to 4 components
+ Reduced wool to string conversion from 2 string to 1 string
+ Fixed zombies holding their tools backwards
+ Fixed salads and other soups making the sawing noise

## [Sugarcane]
+ Sugarcane mechanics have been overhauled
+ Sugarcane now naturally generates it's bottom stem as rooted
+ Newly planted sugarcane will slowly root over time
+ Rooting process takes around a full moon cycle
+ Rooted sugarcane will grow sugarcane around vanilla rates, not dependent on climate

## [Development]
+ New rendering implementation for "crossed-squares" rendered blocks (render type 1)
+ New hardness overload method for variable hardness blocks

